  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\(injective)::function:from{A}:to{B}]\nRefines: f(x__)\nwhen: A, B is \\set\nsatisfies:\n. forAll: x1, x2 \"in\" A\n  then:\n  . if: f(x1) = f(x2)\n    then: x1 = x2\nDocumented:\n. adjective: \"injective\"\n. written: \"\\operatorname{injective}\"\n. description: \"A function $f$ is injective when $f(x) = f(y)$ implies $x = y$ for all $x, y$ in its domain; distinct inputs yield distinct outputs.\"\nId: \"2e0546a7-28b9-4d11-a575-a3ee3fb45f3d\"",
